# Cursor AI Rules for Hair Loss Diagnosis & Treatment Platform

## Project Overview
This is a complete Hair Loss Diagnosis & Treatment Platform built with Laravel 11 backend and React 19 frontend applications.

## Code Standards
- Use Laravel 11+ with proper Eloquent ORM and migrations
- Use React 19+ with TypeScript and functional components
- Follow PSR-12 coding standards for PHP
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Implement proper error handling and validation

## File Organization
- Backend: Laravel 11 in root directory
- Frontend: React apps in `frontend/` directory
- Setup scripts: Shell scripts for Unix/Linux/macOS and batch files for Windows
- Documentation: Comprehensive setup and usage guides

## Prompt Tracking
- Every significant prompt and response should be documented
- Update `prompts.json` with prompt metadata
- Create prompt files in `prompts/` directory when needed
- Include prompt references in generated code comments

## Development Workflow
- Use the provided setup scripts for local development
- Test all functionality before deployment
- Maintain proper error handling and user feedback
- Keep documentation updated with any changes

## Key Features
- Multi-role authentication (Patient, Dermatologist, Admin)
- Hair loss assessment quiz with AI recommendations
- Real-time chat between patients and dermatologists
- Payment integration with Razorpay
- Email notification system
- Comprehensive admin panel

## Setup Instructions
- Use `setup-backend.bat` for Windows backend setup
- Use `setup-patient.bat`, `setup-dermatologist.bat`, `setup-admin.bat` for frontend apps
- Use `setup-all.bat` for complete platform setup
- Follow the comprehensive `SETUP.md` guide for detailed instructions
